Class PbfEntity<T extends org.openstreetmap.osmosis.core.domain.v0_6.Entity>

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.mesakit.map.data.formats.pbf.model.entities.PbfEntity<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.string.AsString, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.string.StringFormattable, Iterable<org.openstreetmap.osmosis.core.domain.v0_6.Tag>
Direct Known Subclasses:
PbfNode, PbfRelation, PbfWay
public abstract class PbfEntity<T extends org.openstreetmap.osmosis.core.domain.v0_6.Entity> extends Object implements com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.string.StringFormattable, Iterable<org.openstreetmap.osmosis.core.domain.v0_6.Tag>
This wrapper (and PbfNode, PbfWay and PbfRelation subclasses) adds a slight amount of overhead, but accessing tags and especially constructing tag maps is such a hotspot that it makes sense to add this wrapper. The major benefit is that the PbfTagMap associated with an entity is cached along with the object, which ensures that different use points have access to a single tag map for the entity without the need to construct a map that has potentially already been constructed. In addition to this benefit, this class and its subclasses provide convenient methods for working with entities.
Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
